      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPECIALS POSTER (7) finished fourth last start, beaten 17 metres at Shepparton over 1690m. No harm in drawing here with the sprint lane to rely upon. Leading hope in a similar race. BETTING ATTACK (1) settled close to the pace but didn't find enough in the end and could only manage tenth last start over 2150m at Bendigo, that effort coming after a minor placing at Ballarat the run before. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run and rates a leading hope if anywhere near his best. MACHFREDDY (2) is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish third at Mt Gambier over 1780m. Genuine top-three threat. STOLEN ONE (4) ended last prep with an eighth at Riverina Paceway over 1740m three-and-a-half months ago. Can open this campaign with a much more positive effort.",
